



To Captains Savage and McKenzie.
[Alexandria, 16 December 1755]



You are ordered to remain here with your Recruits until further Orders. So soon as you arrive here, your men will be supplied with Clothes by applying to Major Carlyle. If any of your
[217]
men should desert, you are to use your utmost diligence in pursuing and apprehending them, by immediately advertising, and sending a party or parties after them.

Alexandria: December 16, 1755.

